						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Banshaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Now I was able to make it work because of a little bit of luck. When it was time to select my bank, I saw in the neotoxin code that he was shifting the bit left once before writing the bank number.</div>
<br />iNES bank numbers (16 KiB each) need to be shifted to the left once before they will work as MMC3 bank numbers (8 KiB each). Then bit 0 selects the lower half or upper half of the 16 KiB bank.</div>

