					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Banshaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Do most people define their banks in 16k or 8k chunks? I guess it depends on what inside.</div>
<br />And on the mapper you are using. With the MMC3 it makes sense to have the banks as 8KB chunks, unless you plan on always switching them in pairs, in which case you could treat them as 16KB banks.
<br />
<br />There are many things that seem confusing at first, because of the names used, the old iNES header, and so on. Try to see past these conventions and understand what's going on. Bankswitching is just the mapper controlling the higher address lines of the chip depending on what areas of memory are being accessed. There really isn't such thing as a "bank", this is just a name to make the concept easier to grasp (but sometimes that doesn't allow people to see the whole picture).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
